cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with resource and power allocation in wireless networks. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves the allocation of resources based on the quality of the desired signal and frequency-selective fading. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper presents a fuzzy logic system for inter-cell interference coordination. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a potential category as the paper discusses system performance improvements in terms of throughput and coverage. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper utilises a fuzzy logic system for resource allocation.
